# /etc/opk/providers — trusted OIDC providers
#
# Format: ISSUER  CLIENT_ID  EXPIRATION_POLICY
#
# ISSUER             — must match the "iss" claim in the OIDC token.
# CLIENT_ID          — must match the "aud" claim.
# EXPIRATION_POLICY  — how long a token remains valid after issue (e.g. 24h).
#
# Google example:
https://accounts.google.com                                          YOUR_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID          24h
#
# Azure AD / Microsoft Entra example:
https://login.microsoftonline.com/YOUR_TENANT_ID/v2.0               YOUR_AZURE_CLIENT_ID           24h
